The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Bengal in final
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: Bengal have reached the final of the national under-21 football championship being played in Jamalpur. According to information received here on Wednesday, Bengal beat Bihar 3-0 in the semi-final. They will take on Punjab in Fridays final. Rahim Nabi (12th minute), Habib Ali (22nd) and Gouranga Dutta (86th) scored for Bengal. Punjab beat Goa 3-2 in the other match, which was abandoned on Tuesday with 24 minutes remaining. The remaining part of the match was played on Wednesday and Punjab made most of their 2-0 lead. Super Division It has been learnt that East Bengals first match in the Super Division league will be on July 10. Mohun Bagan are expected to start two days before that. The Salt Lake Stadium will undergo renovation from July 25 to get ready for the September 8 World Cup qualifier between India and Japan. Super Divisions exhibition matches in the first phase will thus have to be completed by July 25. Similarly, exhibition matches in the second phase will be played after September 8. The Super Division league is expected to be over by September 25, after which the IFA Shield will be held. As things stand now, four city teams, two from Goa, Mahindra United and one foreign team will take part. If the IFA succeeds in roping in another foreign team, just one team from Goa will be invited. The IFA is also trying to invite filmstar Mithun Chakraborty for its annual prize distribution function to be held in Rabindra Sadan on June 19. Meanwhile, AFC instructor Gabriel Joseph will soon conduct a C licence course for coaches at the SAI Eastern Centre. Twenty-four from Bengal, including four women, will attend the programme. Among notables are Compton Dutta, Biswajit das and Hemanta Dora.  Copyright 
